WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.190
"The Americans."

2
00:00:02.190 --> 00:00:04.300
Um. the surveillance
reports you requested.

3
00:00:04.300 --> 00:00:07.040
Alexandria. Virginia.
the week of January 23rd.

4
00:00:07.040 --> 00:00:09.890
The DOD meeting was on the same
day as that horrible murder.

5
00:00:09.890 --> 00:00:12.220
You mean that couple
and their daughter?

6
00:00:12.220 --> 00:00:13.820
That scared the hell out of me.

7
00:00:13.820 --> 00:00:15.420
Get me all the files
and physical evidence

8
00:00:15.420 --> 00:00:16.780
connected to those murders.

9
00:00:16.780 --> 00:00:18.050
don't you
let me handle this?

10
00:00:18.050 --> 00:00:20.720
Mullin's a camera buff.
classical music lover.

11
00:00:20.720 --> 00:00:21.850
There's a million
ways in on this.

12
00:00:21.850 --> 00:00:23.510
I'm so sorry.

13
00:00:23.510 --> 00:00:25.960
I'm just having a hard time.

14
00:00:25.960 --> 00:00:27.070
What are you doing here?

15
00:00:27.070 --> 00:00:29.510
It's OK cause uh.
I'm with Septic.

16
00:00:29.510 --> 00:00:32.440
Hey. hey. he's got a
cam...

17
00:00:36.400 --> 00:00:38.830
Are we going to start going
to church every Sunday now?

18
00:00:38.830 --> 00:00:41.060
$600?

19
00:00:41.060 --> 00:00:42.370
That was all you had.

20
00:00:42.370 --> 00:00:43.160
Lie to us.

21
00:00:43.160 --> 00:00:43.480
Dad!

22
00:00:43.480 --> 00:00:43.930
Stop it!

23
00:00:43.930 --> 00:00:44.630
Why?

24
00:00:44.630 --> 00:00:45.930
Does this book tell
you to do that?

25
00:00:45.930 --> 00:00:46.690
Phillip.

26
00:00:46.690 --> 00:00:49.910
You respect Jesus but not us?

27
00:00:49.910 --> 00:00:51.210
You didn't have
a choice. Philip.

28
00:00:51.210 --> 00:00:52.110
This is war.

29
00:00:52.110 --> 00:00:52.810
Regan...

30
00:00:52.810 --> 00:00:55.050
I don't need the speech.

31
00:00:55.050 --> 00:00:56.160
I know it's war.

32
00:00:56.160 --> 00:00:57.440
This is easier for.

33
00:00:57.440 --> 00:00:59.100
You think it's easy for me?

34
00:00:59.100 --> 00:01:00.090
What I do?

35
00:01:02.000 --> 00:01:08.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

36
00:01:19.350 --> 00:01:20.830
Hi.

37
00:01:20.830 --> 00:01:23.300
Hey.

38
00:01:23.300 --> 00:01:24.620
I didn't mean to wake you.

39
00:01:27.600 --> 00:01:31.140
No. I... wasn't really sleeping.

40
00:01:37.300 --> 00:01:38.070
You hungry?

41
00:01:56.420 --> 00:01:59.130
I want to talk to Paige.

42
00:01:59.130 --> 00:02:01.830
Tell her I'm sorry.

43
00:02:01.830 --> 00:02:02.530
No.

44
00:02:05.470 --> 00:02:07.440
You weren't wrong.

45
00:02:07.440 --> 00:02:08.910
She was disrespecting us.

46
00:02:12.350 --> 00:02:14.930
I made her clean the
kitchen. mop the floor.

47
00:02:27.170 --> 00:02:29.160
Come here.

48
00:02:29.160 --> 00:02:30.160
Take this off.

49
00:02:46.630 --> 00:02:48.120
You look tired.

50
00:03:44.510 --> 00:03:45.970
You back already?

51
00:03:45.970 --> 00:03:48.430
Yeah. I had a
personal emergency.

52
00:03:48.430 --> 00:03:49.870
Sorry to hear it. man.

53
00:03:49.870 --> 00:03:52.110
Anything I can do?

54
00:03:52.110 --> 00:03:55.000
Eh. some things in live you
can only handle yourself.

55
00:03:55.000 --> 00:03:56.830
I hear that.

56
00:03:56.830 --> 00:03:57.840
Good luck.

57
00:03:57.840 --> 00:03:58.540
Thanks.

58
00:04:35.530 --> 00:04:36.230
Mm-hmm.

59
00:04:39.480 --> 00:04:40.660
Yes.

60
00:04:40.660 --> 00:04:41.360
Thank you.

61
00:05:18.490 --> 00:05:19.390
Good morning.

62
00:05:19.390 --> 00:05:21.450
I'm calling from the JD
Pierce elementary school

63
00:05:21.450 --> 00:05:25.740
in Mezzo Heights regarding
our 17th Annual fund drive.

64
00:05:25.740 --> 00:05:27.010
We'd be happy to
make a contribution.

65
00:05:35.800 --> 00:05:37.110
Leggo my eggo.

66
00:05:37.110 --> 00:05:37.870
It's not an eggo.

67
00:05:37.870 --> 00:05:38.600
mom made it.

68
00:05:38.600 --> 00:05:39.670
Oh.

69
00:05:39.670 --> 00:05:40.370
In that case.

70
00:05:40.370 --> 00:05:42.570
Put us down for $25. please.

71
00:05:42.570 --> 00:05:45.520
So Henry. I signed you up for
a math club after school today.

72
00:05:45.520 --> 00:05:46.640
What?

73
00:05:46.640 --> 00:05:48.750
April fools!

74
00:05:48.750 --> 00:05:50.300
April Fool's is in a week. Dad.

75
00:05:52.730 --> 00:05:53.430
Yeah. I know.

76
00:05:53.430 --> 00:05:55.780
Just practicing.

77
00:05:55.780 --> 00:05:56.540
Come on. Henry.

78
00:06:02.680 --> 00:06:03.900
She'll be fine.

79
00:06:03.900 --> 00:06:05.610
Yeah.

80
00:06:05.610 --> 00:06:06.800
We have to get to the office.

81
00:06:13.380 --> 00:06:16.990
Sounds like things got
rough in training camp.

82
00:06:16.990 --> 00:06:18.180
Are you OK?

83
00:06:18.180 --> 00:06:19.650
We're fine.

84
00:06:19.650 --> 00:06:22.380
It was a dangerous mission.
and a successful one.

85
00:06:22.380 --> 00:06:24.630
The Senator is very pleased.

86
00:06:24.630 --> 00:06:26.500
So where do our photos wind up?

87
00:06:26.500 --> 00:06:29.150
We're leaking them to a
newspaper in South America.

88
00:06:29.150 --> 00:06:31.440
They'll make their
way to Capitol Hill.

89
00:06:31.440 --> 00:06:33.020
The important thing
is you're safe.

90
00:06:38.380 --> 00:06:39.470
Something's come up.

91
00:06:39.470 --> 00:06:41.300
It's time sensitive.

92
00:06:41.300 --> 00:06:43.840
We'd like you to tackle it
if you feel you're ready.

93
00:06:46.940 --> 00:06:48.850
A Pakistani
delegation is arriving

94
00:06:48.850 --> 00:06:51.030
in Washington today for talks.

95
00:06:51.030 --> 00:06:54.870
20 diplomats. but 5 of them are
ISI. Covert Action Division.

96
00:06:54.870 --> 00:06:55.940
To meet with the CIA?

97
00:06:55.940 --> 00:06:56.640
Yes.

98
00:06:56.640 --> 00:06:58.870
The Americans are stepping
up their arms shipments

99
00:06:58.870 --> 00:07:00.980
through Pakistan
to the Mujahideen.

100
00:07:00.980 --> 00:07:03.240
We're getting hit hard this year
throughout the African tribal

101
00:07:03.240 --> 00:07:05.360
regions. especially
in the southeast.

102
00:07:05.360 --> 00:07:08.390
We need someone on the inside.

103
00:07:08.390 --> 00:07:09.630
Who have you got?

104
00:07:09.630 --> 00:07:10.960
Yousaf Rana.

105
00:07:10.960 --> 00:07:13.670
Number two guy. Covert Action.

106
00:07:13.670 --> 00:07:16.270
Highly respected. next in
line to run the division.

107
00:07:16.270 --> 00:07:17.540
We assessed him
four years ago when

108
00:07:17.540 --> 00:07:19.480
he was in the
Netherlands on a posting.

109
00:07:19.480 --> 00:07:22.830
Oxford educated. former
professional cricket player.

110
00:07:22.830 --> 00:07:24.840
Potentially susceptible.

111
00:07:24.840 --> 00:07:28.000
Dated European women.
one of the Guinness girls.

112
00:07:28.000 --> 00:07:29.870
How long they here?

113
00:07:29.870 --> 00:07:31.190
Four days.

114
00:07:31.190 --> 00:07:33.890
That's not much time.

115
00:07:33.890 --> 00:07:34.590
We'll be fine.

116
00:07:59.360 --> 00:08:02.350
My government has agreed to
accept your police department's

117
00:08:02.350 --> 00:08:06.670
version of events surrounding
Vlad Kosygin's death.

118
00:08:06.670 --> 00:08:08.990
I got a call
early this morning.

119
00:08:08.990 --> 00:08:10.220
Is that why you're here?

120
00:08:10.220 --> 00:08:12.980
To congratulate me
on my reinstatement?

121
00:08:12.980 --> 00:08:15.670
Or are you trying to tell
me you know where I live?

122
00:08:15.670 --> 00:08:18.800
You could've destroyed us both.

123
00:08:18.800 --> 00:08:21.250
Mutually assured destruction.

124
00:08:21.250 --> 00:08:22.460
Keeps the world spinning.

125
00:08:29.390 --> 00:08:32.700
He was a 23-year-old
first year officer.

126
00:08:32.700 --> 00:08:35.380
He'd been here three months.

127
00:08:35.380 --> 00:08:37.040
Would have washed out in a year.

128
00:08:37.040 --> 00:08:40.500
Didn't have the
stomach for the trade.

129
00:08:40.500 --> 00:08:42.080
He wanted to be a doctor.

130
00:08:42.080 --> 00:08:43.100
He should have been a doctor.

131
00:08:45.710 --> 00:08:49.170
I had a friend. Chris Amador.

132
00:08:49.170 --> 00:08:51.100
Funny guy.

133
00:08:51.100 --> 00:08:53.500
What we like to
call a character.

134
00:08:53.500 --> 00:08:56.760
He could light up a room.

135
00:08:56.760 --> 00:08:58.680
You target our people.
we target yours.

136
00:09:03.600 --> 00:09:07.250
You have a beautiful
home. Agent Gaad.

137
00:09:07.250 --> 00:09:10.680
I'd give you a tour.
but I'm due back at work.

138
00:09:37.130 --> 00:09:41.950
Excuse me. is this your paper?

139
00:09:41.950 --> 00:09:43.940
Just leave me the crossword.

140
00:09:43.940 --> 00:09:46.930
Sunday was a bear. wasn't it?

141
00:09:46.930 --> 00:09:48.420
Let's see.

142
00:09:48.420 --> 00:09:49.420
Thank you.

143
00:10:01.870 --> 00:10:02.860
They're here.

144
00:10:07.840 --> 00:10:09.340
Pleasure to meet you.

145
00:10:09.340 --> 00:10:10.330
How do you do. sir?

146
00:10:10.330 --> 00:10:11.830
Pleasure.

147
00:10:11.830 --> 00:10:12.820
Very nice to meet you.

148
00:10:12.820 --> 00:10:13.820
Let's go chat.

149
00:10:30.510 --> 00:10:31.600
How'd it go with Yousaf?

150
00:10:31.600 --> 00:10:34.290
It shouldn't be a problem.

151
00:10:34.290 --> 00:10:35.580
I think we should use Annelise.

152
00:10:40.080 --> 00:10:40.850
You do?

153
00:10:40.850 --> 00:10:41.550
Yeah.

154
00:10:41.550 --> 00:10:45.290
This guy's been ISI
for eight years.

155
00:10:45.290 --> 00:10:46.160
He's experienced.

156
00:10:46.160 --> 00:10:48.790
He'll be suspicious of a woman
he meets in a bar or hotel

157
00:10:48.790 --> 00:10:51.050
lobby. but the
wife of the Deputy

158
00:10:51.050 --> 00:10:52.060
Undersecretary of Defence?

159
00:10:54.680 --> 00:10:58.290
But Annelise has no experience
running something like this.

160
00:10:58.290 --> 00:11:00.140
Yeah. maybe to make
the initial contact.

161
00:11:00.140 --> 00:11:03.810
But she'd have to keep it
going for months. maybe years.

162
00:11:03.810 --> 00:11:06.790
I'll get her there.

163
00:11:06.790 --> 00:11:07.980
I can do my job. Phillip.

164
00:11:07.980 --> 00:11:11.340
I know you can. but this
time you don't have to.

165
00:11:14.670 --> 00:11:19.270
When was the last time
you spoke to Annelise?

166
00:11:19.270 --> 00:11:20.530
Six weeks ago.

167
00:11:20.530 --> 00:11:22.140
Trust me. this is
the better move.

168
00:11:42.690 --> 00:11:45.080
Welcome back. sir.

169
00:11:45.080 --> 00:11:46.980
Congratulations.

170
00:11:46.980 --> 00:11:49.480
What's all this?

171
00:11:49.480 --> 00:11:51.800
Oleg Burov.

172
00:11:51.800 --> 00:11:53.420
Arrives in this
country January 8th

173
00:11:53.420 --> 00:11:56.390
to head up Line X
for the Rezidentura.

174
00:11:56.390 --> 00:11:58.120
Two weeks later. there's a
meeting of all the groups

175
00:11:58.120 --> 00:12:00.210
working with the DOD
on stealth technology.

176
00:12:00.210 --> 00:12:02.330
That's here.

177
00:12:02.330 --> 00:12:05.900
That same weekend there's a
family murdered in a hotel room

178
00:12:05.900 --> 00:12:07.680
here.

179
00:12:07.680 --> 00:12:08.380
Close.

180
00:12:08.380 --> 00:12:09.080
Mm-hmm.

181
00:12:09.080 --> 00:12:10.610
Too close.

182
00:12:10.610 --> 00:12:12.440
Do you think Burov is involved?

183
00:12:12.440 --> 00:12:14.090
I can't make a
direct connection.

184
00:12:14.090 --> 00:12:16.940
Look. look.

185
00:12:16.940 --> 00:12:22.170
No suspects. no motive. shot
to death in a hotel room

186
00:12:22.170 --> 00:12:24.660
two miles away from
a top secret meeting.

187
00:12:24.660 --> 00:12:27.740
The dead couple.
any DOD connection?

188
00:12:27.740 --> 00:12:28.810
I haven't found any.

189
00:12:33.530 --> 00:12:36.280
Why where were they
there at the hotel?

190
00:12:36.280 --> 00:12:40.280
Their son told the police
they were on a family vacation.

191
00:12:40.280 --> 00:12:42.340
You ever take a briefcase
with you on vacation?

192
00:12:45.120 --> 00:12:45.820
No.

193
00:13:19.940 --> 00:13:20.750
Holy shit.

194
00:13:20.750 --> 00:13:22.810
Yeah.

195
00:13:22.810 --> 00:13:25.840
Drug dealers and
smugglers. they rig up

196
00:13:25.840 --> 00:13:30.010
concealments. but not like this.

197
00:13:30.010 --> 00:13:31.080
This is an intelligence service.

198
00:13:39.378 --> 00:13:41.398
It's the corner table.

199
00:13:44.398 --> 00:13:47.858
You look spectacular.

200
00:13:47.858 --> 00:13:48.558
Thank you.

201
00:13:48.558 --> 00:13:50.698
So do you.

202
00:13:50.698 --> 00:13:52.998
We could skip this.

203
00:13:52.998 --> 00:13:56.618
Go upstairs. have room service.

204
00:13:56.618 --> 00:13:58.488
I can't do that.

205
00:13:58.488 --> 00:14:02.308
Douglas and I have been
trying to make things work.

206
00:14:02.308 --> 00:14:03.878
Oh.

207
00:14:03.878 --> 00:14:05.428
He's a wonderful man.

208
00:14:05.428 --> 00:14:08.228
He's so understanding.

209
00:14:08.228 --> 00:14:09.548
Well then good for you.

210
00:14:09.548 --> 00:14:13.048
I... I have nothing but respect
for the great institution

211
00:14:13.048 --> 00:14:15.428
of marriage or
those who can do it.

212
00:14:19.738 --> 00:14:22.568
Anyway. that's not why I called.

213
00:14:22.568 --> 00:14:25.688
It's not?

214
00:14:25.688 --> 00:14:29.408
Swedish intelligence needs you.

215
00:14:29.408 --> 00:14:32.078
Are you serious?

216
00:14:32.078 --> 00:14:34.508
There's a dinner tonight in
the home of William Clark.

217
00:14:34.508 --> 00:14:37.148
the new head of the
National Security Council.

218
00:14:37.148 --> 00:14:38.718
You are serious.

219
00:14:38.718 --> 00:14:40.938
A Pakistani delegation
will be there.

220
00:14:40.938 --> 00:14:46.468
and I would like you
to talk to this man.

221
00:14:46.468 --> 00:14:47.948
Who is he?

222
00:14:47.948 --> 00:14:52.058
He's not a bad man.
but dangerous things

223
00:14:52.058 --> 00:14:54.228
are happening in Pakistan.

224
00:14:54.228 --> 00:14:58.718
Things that could
threaten all of Europe.

225
00:14:58.718 --> 00:15:01.958
Annelise. it's important.

226
00:15:01.958 --> 00:15:03.348
I don't think
we're even invited

227
00:15:03.348 --> 00:15:06.808
to a party at William
Clark's house.

228
00:15:06.808 --> 00:15:08.958
How hard would it
be for the Deputy

229
00:15:08.958 --> 00:15:12.228
Undersecretary of
Defence to get invited?

230
00:15:12.228 --> 00:15:12.928
Hm.

231
00:15:17.198 --> 00:15:18.758
He's handsome.

232
00:15:18.758 --> 00:15:19.458
And powerful.

233
00:15:23.268 --> 00:15:24.728
What do you need me to do?

234
00:15:50.518 --> 00:15:51.218
Hey. Dad.

235
00:15:51.218 --> 00:15:51.918
Do you have a minute?

236
00:15:54.078 --> 00:15:54.778
Sure.

237
00:15:57.658 --> 00:15:58.828
I've come to a decision.

238
00:16:01.928 --> 00:16:03.308
Here's what I want
to do this summer.

239
00:16:11.078 --> 00:16:12.868
Cedar Grove Fellowship Camp?

240
00:16:15.858 --> 00:16:18.948
Is this from church?

241
00:16:18.948 --> 00:16:21.488
Look. I know it's
not your thing.

242
00:16:21.488 --> 00:16:23.538
but it's not all
preachy and everything.

243
00:16:23.538 --> 00:16:25.618
It's just... it's normal.

244
00:16:25.618 --> 00:16:27.838
Swimming and hiking
and they teach

245
00:16:27.838 --> 00:16:29.898
you teamwork and social values.

246
00:16:29.898 --> 00:16:31.408
Three months?

247
00:16:31.408 --> 00:16:33.328
That's the summer.

248
00:16:33.328 --> 00:16:34.178
It's a summer camp.

249
00:16:37.288 --> 00:16:38.718
I'm not even asking for money.

250
00:16:38.718 --> 00:16:41.128
I'll be a CIT.

251
00:16:41.128 --> 00:16:44.448
Counsellor in Training.

252
00:16:46.398 --> 00:16:48.028
OK.

253
00:16:48.028 --> 00:16:50.528
I'll uh... I'll talk to your mom.

254
00:16:50.528 --> 00:16:53.178
All right. but I really
need to get this in.

255
00:16:53.178 --> 00:16:56.058
It's almost April and
it starts June 5th.

256
00:16:56.058 --> 00:16:58.888
And that's like soon.

257
00:16:58.888 --> 00:17:00.928
And you're old enough
to be a counsellor?

258
00:17:00.928 --> 00:17:01.818
Yeah.

259
00:17:01.818 --> 00:17:03.388
Well. in training.

260
00:17:03.388 --> 00:17:04.088
Wow.

261
00:17:11.928 --> 00:17:12.628
OK. counsellor.

262
00:20:47.028 --> 00:20:48.328
Is she kidding?

263
00:20:48.328 --> 00:20:49.778
She can get a job
for the summer.

264
00:20:49.778 --> 00:20:52.998
She can do a paper route or take
tickets at the movie theatre.

265
00:20:52.998 --> 00:20:54.028
Well...

266
00:20:54.028 --> 00:20:55.148
You don't agree?

267
00:20:55.148 --> 00:20:57.578
I worry if we say
no. she just digs in.

268
00:20:57.578 --> 00:20:59.908
But if we say yes. she
comes home a Jesus freak.

269
00:20:59.908 --> 00:21:02.778
Well then maybe we just need
to let her figure it out.

270
00:21:02.778 --> 00:21:05.608
I'm not trusting someone
else with our daughter's mind.

271
00:21:05.608 --> 00:21:07.878
What if we say no and
she does something else?

272
00:21:07.878 --> 00:21:11.328
Like drinking or drugs?

273
00:21:11.328 --> 00:21:14.398
I'll take my chances.

274
00:21:14.398 --> 00:21:15.228
Well then maybe...

275
00:21:15.228 --> 00:21:16.318
Where are we with Annelise?

276
00:21:21.318 --> 00:21:23.018
What'd you order?

277
00:21:23.018 --> 00:21:25.378
All this sneaking around
gives me an appetite.

278
00:21:29.988 --> 00:21:31.398
So how'd it go?

279
00:21:31.398 --> 00:21:34.318
Good. I think.

280
00:21:34.318 --> 00:21:35.658
No. it was good.

281
00:21:35.658 --> 00:21:39.268
I felt like I was doing
something important.

282
00:21:39.268 --> 00:21:40.518
Tell me.

283
00:21:40.518 --> 00:21:42.108
Well Yousaf kept
checking me out

284
00:21:42.108 --> 00:21:43.588
during Bill Clark's
warmonger toast.

285
00:21:46.448 --> 00:21:49.108
Then I got Jeanne
Kirkpatrick to introduce us.

286
00:21:49.108 --> 00:21:50.988
We ended up on the
patio smoking those...

287
00:21:50.988 --> 00:21:52.338
those little
Japanese cigarettes.

288
00:21:52.338 --> 00:21:53.908
You know. the ones that
come in the blue pack?

289
00:21:53.908 --> 00:21:56.688
What did you find out?

290
00:21:56.688 --> 00:22:00.398
Well he's here on some
big. secret mission.

291
00:22:00.398 --> 00:22:03.358
But he doesn't really
know that much about it.

292
00:22:03.358 --> 00:22:05.308
What do you mean?

293
00:22:05.308 --> 00:22:07.028
He's the number two.

294
00:22:07.028 --> 00:22:09.798
And his boss. this Javid Parvez?

295
00:22:09.798 --> 00:22:12.458
Well. Javid doesn't really
keep him in the loop.

296
00:22:12.458 --> 00:22:15.538
Yousaf knows diddly squat.

297
00:22:15.538 --> 00:22:18.058
He's set to get Javid's
job in a couple years. so.

298
00:22:19.538 --> 00:22:21.228
We can't wait a couple years.

299
00:22:21.228 --> 00:22:23.868
Do you want me
to go after Javid?

300
00:22:23.868 --> 00:22:25.348
No.

301
00:22:25.348 --> 00:22:26.718
No. you... you've been great.

302
00:22:26.718 --> 00:22:28.118
Really great.

303
00:22:28.118 --> 00:22:30.078
How did you leave
things with Yousaf?

304
00:22:30.078 --> 00:22:32.248
He said he wants to see
me again before he leaves.

305
00:22:35.928 --> 00:22:38.678
I want to shut down a mission.

306
00:22:38.678 --> 00:22:40.088
Shut it down?

307
00:22:40.088 --> 00:22:40.788
Yeah.

308
00:22:40.788 --> 00:22:42.388
Yousaf's boss keeps
him in the dark.

309
00:22:42.388 --> 00:22:43.418
Doesn't let him in on anything.

310
00:22:43.418 --> 00:22:45.238
We're just waisting our time.

311
00:22:45.238 --> 00:22:48.238
Reagan's trying to turn
Afghanistan into our Vietnam.

312
00:22:48.238 --> 00:22:50.178
We've all got brothers
fighting there.

313
00:22:50.178 --> 00:22:51.038
Fathers. sons.

314
00:22:51.038 --> 00:22:53.978
I understand that.
but we have a problem.

315
00:22:53.978 --> 00:22:56.588
All right.

316
00:22:56.588 --> 00:22:58.108
Let me talk to the Centre.

317
00:22:58.108 --> 00:23:01.748
Meanwhile. have Elizabeth
keep working the target.

318
00:23:01.748 --> 00:23:04.448
Annelise is working it.

319
00:23:04.448 --> 00:23:06.528
That doesn't seem
like the best way.

320
00:23:06.528 --> 00:23:10.228
Well. the intel on
Javid came from her.

321
00:23:10.228 --> 00:23:12.578
Can we move on?

322
00:23:12.578 --> 00:23:14.358
I am not a dolt. Philip.

323
00:23:14.358 --> 00:23:15.188
I didn't think you were.

324
00:23:15.188 --> 00:23:17.268
I am responsible
for you. and I expect

325
00:23:17.268 --> 00:23:18.898
a certain amount of respect.

326
00:23:18.898 --> 00:23:22.018
If you mess up. my head
will roll. not yours.

327
00:23:22.018 --> 00:23:24.588
No. if we mess up. we're dead.

328
00:23:24.588 --> 00:23:25.858
So I'll wait for
word from the Centre.

329
00:23:38.955 --> 00:23:40.455
You armed?

330
00:23:40.455 --> 00:23:43.235
Yeah.

331
00:23:43.235 --> 00:23:45.535
It's still cold out there.

332
00:23:45.535 --> 00:23:48.815
Judge Akin. case 41967P.

333
00:23:48.815 --> 00:23:50.235
You like the cherry blossoms?

334
00:23:50.235 --> 00:23:51.535
Never miss 'em.

335
00:23:51.535 --> 00:23:52.235
And the number?

336
00:23:52.235 --> 00:23:54.565
Yeah.

337
00:23:54.565 --> 00:23:57.105
As long as I've been
here. they still

338
00:23:57.105 --> 00:23:59.555
knock me out year after year.

339
00:23:59.555 --> 00:24:00.255
OK.

340
00:24:13.965 --> 00:24:16.365
It looks like this
number is unassigned.

341
00:24:16.365 --> 00:24:18.335
Best I can do is give
you a junction box.

342
00:24:18.335 --> 00:24:20.255
That'd be great. Mrs. Portman.

343
00:24:20.255 --> 00:24:24.525
Corner of Grand street and
Mohawk Lane in Bethesda.

344
00:24:24.525 --> 00:24:29.175
Pier number 1457.

345
00:24:29.175 --> 00:24:30.515
Thanks for this.

346
00:24:30.515 --> 00:24:31.395
You did some good today.

347
00:24:36.925 --> 00:24:38.615
We're finding everything
out that we can.

348
00:24:38.615 --> 00:24:40.635
Where they worked.
hobbies. phone records.

349
00:24:40.635 --> 00:24:42.355
What they did in
their spare time.

350
00:24:42.355 --> 00:24:44.055
Matching the names
of birth certificates

351
00:24:44.055 --> 00:24:45.405
of people who died young.

352
00:24:45.405 --> 00:24:47.055
Tracing border crossing records.

353
00:24:47.055 --> 00:24:48.935
Speak to the Metro Police?

354
00:24:48.935 --> 00:24:50.485
Yeah. they've got nothing.

355
00:24:50.485 --> 00:24:52.075
They didn't know what
they were looking for.

356
00:24:52.075 --> 00:24:53.545
Wasn't there a son?

357
00:24:53.545 --> 00:24:55.035
He was down at the
pool when it happened.

358
00:24:55.035 --> 00:24:57.785
Didn't see anything til
he came up and found them.

359
00:24:57.785 --> 00:24:59.125
If he'd been there
10 minutes earlier...

360
00:24:59.125 --> 00:25:00.805
Kid was lucky.

361
00:25:00.805 --> 00:25:02.015
Not that lucky.

362
00:25:02.015 --> 00:25:05.375
Arkady covered this up well.

363
00:25:05.375 --> 00:25:08.235
Yeah. but he couldn't
have been perfect.

364
00:25:08.235 --> 00:25:09.735
And the killer is
still out there.

365
00:25:15.845 --> 00:25:17.835
I just got a signal.

366
00:25:17.835 --> 00:25:22.975
They want us to kill Yousaf's
boss. Javid Parvez. He goes.

367
00:25:22.975 --> 00:25:26.035
Yousaf steps into the job.

368
00:25:26.035 --> 00:25:29.125
They don't want to
let this one go.

369
00:25:29.125 --> 00:25:31.475
This whole thing's going to be
won or lost in the third world.

370
00:25:34.275 --> 00:25:36.555
Did they give us anything?

371
00:25:36.555 --> 00:25:38.405
Javid's travelling with
virtually no security.

372
00:25:38.405 --> 00:25:40.735
and he takes a swim every
night before dinner.

373
00:25:44.575 --> 00:25:46.905
I'll take care of him.

374
00:25:46.905 --> 00:25:48.705
You'll be with Annelise.

375
00:25:48.705 --> 00:25:51.675
I'll go to the pool.

376
00:25:51.675 --> 00:25:52.635
It's the best move.

377
00:25:56.265 --> 00:25:57.225
Is she ready?

378
00:26:00.475 --> 00:26:01.865
Because we're going
to a lot of trouble

379
00:26:01.865 --> 00:26:04.205
if you can't get her there.

380
00:26:04.205 --> 00:26:04.955
She'll get there.

381
00:26:29.735 --> 00:26:31.255
We're all set.

382
00:26:31.255 --> 00:26:34.905
Dinner in his room.
tomorrow night.

383
00:26:37.795 --> 00:26:39.015
What?

384
00:26:39.015 --> 00:26:41.435
What's wrong?

385
00:26:41.435 --> 00:26:42.975
I'm a little worried.

386
00:26:42.975 --> 00:26:45.365
About?

387
00:26:45.365 --> 00:26:46.065
What?

388
00:26:46.065 --> 00:26:47.645
Is it me?

389
00:26:47.645 --> 00:26:52.225
I'm not sure
you're really ready.

390
00:26:52.225 --> 00:26:53.155
To do what?

391
00:26:55.855 --> 00:26:59.705
Yousaf has to talk to you.

392
00:26:59.705 --> 00:27:02.815
Men talk to me.

393
00:27:05.275 --> 00:27:08.815
But his job is not to talk.

394
00:27:19.495 --> 00:27:20.945
Are you OK?

395
00:27:20.945 --> 00:27:21.875
I've only got five minutes.

396
00:27:21.875 --> 00:27:24.625
Listen. a few
months ago a family

397
00:27:24.625 --> 00:27:26.435
was murdered in a
hotel in Alexandria.

398
00:27:26.435 --> 00:27:27.815
Do you remember that?

399
00:27:27.815 --> 00:27:30.045
It was on the news.

400
00:27:30.045 --> 00:27:31.975
I think they were illegals.

401
00:27:31.975 --> 00:27:33.185
What?

402
00:27:33.185 --> 00:27:34.285
Are you sure?

403
00:27:34.285 --> 00:27:36.285
It looks that way.

404
00:27:36.285 --> 00:27:38.615
It must of been chaos
at the Rezidentura.

405
00:27:38.615 --> 00:27:40.415
They would keep it quiet.

406
00:27:40.415 --> 00:27:43.535
Well you must have heard
something. seen something.

407
00:27:43.535 --> 00:27:45.265
I have nothing to
do with illegals.

408
00:27:45.265 --> 00:27:46.225
You know that. Stan.

409
00:27:46.225 --> 00:27:48.085
Listen. I think
that Burov is here

410
00:27:48.085 --> 00:27:50.065
to steal stealth
technology. and that those

411
00:27:50.065 --> 00:27:51.975
illegals we're
trying to help him.

412
00:27:51.975 --> 00:27:55.595
I don't know how. but I finally
have the clearance to find out.

413
00:27:55.595 --> 00:27:58.315
And when I do. Oleg Burov's
ass will be kicked out

414
00:27:58.315 --> 00:28:01.825
of this country so fast he won't
have time to buckle his pants.

415
00:28:01.825 --> 00:28:04.655
Good.

416
00:28:04.655 --> 00:28:06.615
I'm sorry. I really have to go.

417
00:28:11.535 --> 00:28:14.285
What?

418
00:28:14.285 --> 00:28:14.985
What's the matter?

419
00:28:14.985 --> 00:28:18.425
Tell me.

420
00:28:18.425 --> 00:28:19.905
Sandra is having an affair.

421
00:28:25.825 --> 00:28:28.775
So are you.

422
00:28:32.215 --> 00:28:35.285
It's been bad for so long.

423
00:28:35.285 --> 00:28:41.295
Not bad. not
anything. just dead.

424
00:28:41.295 --> 00:28:43.955
But the funny thing. the crazy
thing is. it's still a shock.

425
00:28:47.875 --> 00:28:50.285
She was a big
part of your life.

426
00:28:50.285 --> 00:28:53.285
You have a son.

427
00:28:53.285 --> 00:28:54.795
I shouldn't be
telling you this.

428
00:28:54.795 --> 00:28:57.715
I...

429
00:28:57.715 --> 00:29:00.635
Makes me sad.

430
00:29:00.635 --> 00:29:03.075
Sad?

431
00:29:03.075 --> 00:29:04.375
To see you in pain.

432
00:29:16.285 --> 00:29:17.765
I really have to get back.

433
00:30:49.197 --> 00:30:50.277
It's not bad.

434
00:30:50.277 --> 00:30:55.157
The second n is a
little off. but...

435
00:30:55.157 --> 00:30:56.167
You went through my garbage?

436
00:30:59.077 --> 00:31:00.517
I was emptying you garbage.

437
00:31:00.517 --> 00:31:01.877
And from now on.
you can empty it.

438
00:31:01.877 --> 00:31:04.427
In fact. you can take out the
trash for the whole house.

439
00:31:07.797 --> 00:31:09.987
I didn't turn it in.

440
00:31:09.987 --> 00:31:11.307
The application.

441
00:31:11.307 --> 00:31:12.967
I know you didn't.

442
00:31:12.967 --> 00:31:14.217
I spoke to Pastor Tim.

443
00:31:14.217 --> 00:31:15.047
You what?

444
00:31:15.047 --> 00:31:16.867
I also told him you will
not be going to camp.

445
00:31:16.867 --> 00:31:17.917
This is bullshit.

446
00:31:17.917 --> 00:31:18.947
Paige.

447
00:31:18.947 --> 00:31:19.907
I'm so sick of this.

448
00:31:19.907 --> 00:31:21.237
Henry breaks into
the neighbour's house

449
00:31:21.237 --> 00:31:22.507
and it's no big deal.

450
00:31:22.507 --> 00:31:25.227
But I want to be a better
person and I'm the bad guy?

451
00:31:25.227 --> 00:31:27.937
You don't know what's
best for you. and I do.

452
00:31:27.937 --> 00:31:29.417
You can't stop me.

453
00:31:29.417 --> 00:31:30.117
Watch me.

454
00:31:41.597 --> 00:31:42.597
Come on now.

455
00:31:42.597 --> 00:31:43.587
Let's get going.

456
00:31:43.587 --> 00:31:44.587
By. Dad.

457
00:31:44.587 --> 00:31:46.087
I'll see you later.

458
00:31:49.077 --> 00:31:50.577
What about some fruit?

459
00:31:50.577 --> 00:31:51.577
Pretzels?

460
00:31:51.577 --> 00:31:52.577
Fruit.

461
00:31:52.577 --> 00:31:53.567
Take an apple.

462
00:31:53.567 --> 00:31:55.067
You can eat in the car.

463
00:31:55.067 --> 00:31:56.067
We really need to get going.

464
00:31:56.067 --> 00:31:57.067
We're going to be late. OK?

465
00:31:57.067 --> 00:31:57.767
OK.

466
00:31:58.557 --> 00:32:00.057
I can't
find it anywhere.

467
00:32:00.057 --> 00:32:01.557
Did you leave
it in the living room?

468
00:32:01.557 --> 00:32:02.557
I don't know.

469
00:32:02.557 --> 00:32:05.087
Well go look.

470
00:32:05.087 --> 00:32:06.857
It's not in here.

471
00:32:06.857 --> 00:32:08.267
Look by the
doll house. honey.

472
00:32:11.737 --> 00:32:12.437
Glo Worm!

473
00:32:49.007 --> 00:32:49.977
He goes alone.

474
00:32:49.977 --> 00:32:51.247
The pool has one entry.

475
00:32:51.247 --> 00:32:52.777
Do it in the swimming pool.

476
00:32:52.777 --> 00:32:54.017
He's swimming.

477
00:32:54.017 --> 00:32:55.257
He has a heart attack.

478
00:32:55.257 --> 00:32:56.177
Right.

479
00:32:56.177 --> 00:33:00.917
You have about an hour.
hour and a half with these.

480
00:33:00.917 --> 00:33:01.927
These are what?

481
00:33:01.927 --> 00:33:03.207
98% effective?

482
00:33:03.207 --> 00:33:03.907
You want two?

483
00:33:06.887 --> 00:33:08.017
Have you seen your daughter?

484
00:33:08.017 --> 00:33:10.257
She's been moping
around since I got home.

485
00:33:10.257 --> 00:33:12.737
And now she's
locked in her room.

486
00:33:12.737 --> 00:33:16.457
I told her she's
not going to camp.

487
00:33:16.457 --> 00:33:18.527
You did?

488
00:33:18.527 --> 00:33:20.877
She was about to forge my
name on the application.

489
00:33:20.877 --> 00:33:23.167
How do you know?

490
00:33:23.167 --> 00:33:24.407
Do you not believe me?

491
00:33:24.407 --> 00:33:25.567
N... no.

492
00:33:25.567 --> 00:33:26.707
No. of course I believe you.

493
00:33:26.707 --> 00:33:29.707
I just didn't think
Paige would do that.

494
00:33:29.707 --> 00:33:31.347
You don't know
what she would do.

495
00:33:31.347 --> 00:33:32.617
You know. you are
so easy on her.

496
00:33:32.617 --> 00:33:34.067
She walks all over you.

497
00:33:34.067 --> 00:33:34.767
That's not true.

498
00:33:34.767 --> 00:33:36.377
She's going to be
eaten alive out there.

499
00:33:36.377 --> 00:33:38.127
She's never going to be
ready for the real world

500
00:33:38.127 --> 00:33:40.417
if we do not get her ready.

501
00:33:40.417 --> 00:33:41.117
We need to go.

502
00:34:33.307 --> 00:34:35.927
You know. I told the
police everything I know.

503
00:34:35.927 --> 00:34:37.167
know.

504
00:34:37.167 --> 00:34:40.737
Well then. what
are you doing here?

505
00:34:40.737 --> 00:34:44.157
Look. I know this has been
a really hard time. Jared.

506
00:34:44.157 --> 00:34:47.347
I uh. can't imagine what
you're going through.

507
00:34:47.347 --> 00:34:49.547
I'm sorry.

508
00:34:49.547 --> 00:34:51.097
But if it's OK with
you. I would like

509
00:34:51.097 --> 00:34:54.877
to ask you a few more questions
about your mom and dad.

510
00:34:59.667 --> 00:35:02.007
To help you find the
people who killed them?

511
00:35:02.007 --> 00:35:03.987
Exactly.

512
00:35:03.987 --> 00:35:05.267
OK.

513
00:35:05.267 --> 00:35:05.967
Thanks.

514
00:35:10.927 --> 00:35:16.147
Did your parents ever
travel outside the country?

515
00:35:16.147 --> 00:35:21.207
Um. they want to Paris for
their wedding anniversary once.

516
00:35:21.207 --> 00:35:23.007
They brought me one of
those little Eiffel towers.

517
00:35:25.577 --> 00:35:26.837
How about friends?

518
00:35:26.837 --> 00:35:31.797
Did they have a lot of
friends or go out a lot?

519
00:35:31.797 --> 00:35:33.067
They didn't have
big drunken parties.

520
00:35:33.067 --> 00:35:34.077
if that's what you mean.

521
00:35:37.357 --> 00:35:38.817
Yeah. uh. they had friends.

522
00:35:42.957 --> 00:35:51.447
I mean... yeah. my mom was on the
PTA and my dad coached T-ball.

523
00:35:56.487 --> 00:35:59.817
Yeah. they were
really great parents.

524
00:35:59.817 --> 00:36:01.047
I bet they were.

525
00:36:04.927 --> 00:36:08.007
But did you ever feel like
there were parts of their life

526
00:36:08.007 --> 00:36:11.657
that you didn't understand
or that were confusing?

527
00:36:15.447 --> 00:36:17.257
What do you mean?

528
00:36:17.257 --> 00:36:18.087
I don't know.

529
00:36:18.087 --> 00:36:20.267
Things like secrets.

530
00:36:20.267 --> 00:36:23.147
Or maybe... maybe they
had place in the house

531
00:36:23.147 --> 00:36:24.227
where they hid things.

532
00:36:24.227 --> 00:36:25.847
No.

533
00:36:25.847 --> 00:36:27.917
Wha... what are you trying to
say that they were criminals.

534
00:36:27.917 --> 00:36:28.717
No. not at all.

535
00:36:28.717 --> 00:36:29.617
All right. well then what?

536
00:36:32.507 --> 00:36:35.497
Look. my... my parents were kind
and they cared about people.

537
00:36:35.497 --> 00:36:39.357
And... you know. and I know
that because I lived with them.

538
00:36:39.357 --> 00:36:40.907
Of course you know. Jared.

539
00:36:43.617 --> 00:36:45.947
I'm not doubting
you for a second.

540
00:36:45.947 --> 00:36:48.837
It sound like they were
really great parents.

541
00:36:51.967 --> 00:36:52.797
But it's funny. you know.

